# Netlify / Cloudflare Pages redirects.
#
# The `vite build` + prerender plugin emits a prerendered `index.html` for
# every known route (e.g. `/why/sso-without-platinum/index.html`). Most
# static hosts auto-resolve `/path` to `/path/index.html` — but SPA routing
# for deep links not covered by prerender still needs a fallback.
#
# This file:
#   1. No explicit rewrites for prerendered routes — the hosts' built-in
#      directory-index resolution handles them.
#   2. A final catch-all so any client-side route (hash anchors, query
#      strings on known paths) still hits the SPA shell with HTTP 200 (not
#      302) so crawlers see the right URL.
#
# If the target host isn't Netlify/Cloudflare Pages, translate this to the
# equivalent config (e.g. `vercel.json` rewrites, or nginx `try_files`).

/*    /index.html   200
